      "id": 75365,
      "name": "blacktek",
      "username": "BlackTek",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/blacktek/{size}/11188_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-04-08T19:20:52.439Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I already use lightest gears on steeper climbs <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>Looking at my power curve at the moment I can sustain 120% of my FTP for 5 minutes, but I got your point.<br>\nHow can I know what is my peak W\u2019 (the max I can obtain)? Based on intervals.icu and GoldenChetah my CP is around 265W and my W\u2019 is around 26k. My FTP is around 260W</p>\n<p>Could a strategy be to train at riding at lower cadence (with SFR) in order to be able to climb at a lower speed and therefore lower power? Normally it\u2019s not easy to ride at very very low cadence on steep climbs.</p>",
