      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/blacktek/{size}/11188_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-04-09T04:43:18.640Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ve a 30t chainring on front and 10/52 back. I know that the final solution is to increase the ftp to use a lower anaerobic reserve. I was also looking at specific workouts to improve on those few special short climbs.</p>\n<p>Is it a complete non sense to try to train lower cadence in order to be able to go slower in steep uphills?</p>\n<p>Normally I see that my natural behaviour is to increase cadence when I\u2019m there. Perhaps in the attempt to complete it sooner and have less pain. Lol</p>",
