      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-04-09T08:55:34.107Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I don\u2019t know about you.  Most of my MTB riding was 80s and 90s but I drop my seat even more going down hill\u2026 But yes all MTB saddle heights are likely posterior chain dominant., I assume.  I guess my point was more experimenting with seat height might give you some additional power.  Obviously moving it back a bit gets more weight on the rear wheel.  I guess I am wondering how much of the climb is in seated position.</p>",
