    {
      "id": 75607,
      "name": "blacktek",
      "username": "BlackTek",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/blacktek/{size}/11188_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-04-13T10:14:37.272Z",
      "cooked": "<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/robert_ucl\">@Robert_UCL</a><br>\nThank you for your feedback; I appreciate it.</p>\n<p>And congrats for climbing Scanuppia, it\u2019s a huge effort which takes your breath away. But it\u2019s the kind of climbs I like <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>So long story short do you recommend to not trying to concentrate on those low term goals, but only on long term ones?<br>\nI like to also have short term goals to build motivation an have targets that you can touch and try to achieve, without waiting too much.</p>\n<p>Doing lot of Z2 helps on the long terms, but it\u2019s not hugely motivating on short term. But it\u2019s also true that we can appreciate how it\u2019s easier to ride while building aerobic capacity.</p>",
      "post_number": 16,
